  </primary_outcome>
  <enrollment type="Anticipated">80</enrollment>
  <condition>Chronic Pain</condition>
  <condition>Smoking</condition>
  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Behavioral</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Smoking cessation counseling</intervention_name>
    <description>Patients will be given a briefing on the benefits of smoking cessation in the peri-procedural period around their interventional pain procedure. They will also be provided an informational sheet from the American Society of Anesthesiologists promoting cessation. The sheet will contain the 1-800-QUITNOW national hotline phone number.&#xD;
Additional an enrollment folder will provided that contains referral information to Cooper's Tobacco Cessation program. This service, free of charge to Cooper Health patients consists of 5 tobacco cessation counselors who use personalized cessation plans, individual and group counseling cessations, Chantix, and education to promote smoking cessation.</description>
  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Chronic Pain of 3 months or greater&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Scheduled for interventional pain procedure&#xD;
&#xD;
        Exclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Cancer related pain&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Current participation in smoking abstinence program&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  History of schizophrenia or other pyschotic disorder&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  History of dementing illness&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Pregnant patients&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Diagnosis of depression or anxiety&#xD;
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
